@page "/about"

<PageTitle>About CP-sight</PageTitle>

<MudContainer MaxWidth="MaxWidth.Medium" Class="mt-4">
    <MudText Typo="Typo.h3" Class="mb-6">About CP-sight</MudText>

    <MudPaper Elevation="2" Class="pa-6 mb-6">
        <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" Class="mb-4">The Problem</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-4">
            Cerebral palsy (CP) is the most common motor disability in childhood, affecting approximately 
            2-3 per 1,000 live births. Early detection is critical—research shows that early intervention 
            during the first years of life can significantly improve outcomes. However, traditional diagnosis 
            often doesn't occur until age 2 or later, missing the optimal window for intervention.
        </MudText>
    </MudPaper>

    <MudPaper Elevation="2" Class="pa-6 mb-6">
        <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" Class="mb-4">Our Solution</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-4">
            CP-sight leverages Prechtl's General Movements Assessment (GMA)—a validated, non-invasive method 
            for early CP detection based on the quality of spontaneous movements in infants. Our AI-powered 
            system analyzes infant videos to detect abnormal movement patterns that are highly predictive 
            of cerebral palsy.
        </MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
            By using computer vision and machine learning, we automate the GMA process, making early screening 
            more accessible and scalable, potentially reaching families who don't have access to specialized 
            clinical assessments.
        </MudText>
    </MudPaper>

    <MudPaper Elevation="2" Class="pa-6 mb-6">
        <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" Class="mb-4">The Science</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-4">
            General Movements Assessment is based on decades of research by Professor Heinz Prechtl and colleagues. 
            The assessment evaluates spontaneous "general movements"—complex movement patterns involving the 
            whole body that are present from fetal life through early infancy.
        </MudText>
        <MudGrid Class="mt-4">
            <MudItem xs="12" md="6">
                <MudList T="string" Dense="true">
                    <MudListItem>
                        <strong>Fidgety Movements (9-20 weeks):</strong> Small, elegant movements that are 
                        crucial for predicting CP. Absence of fidgety movements has >90% specificity for CP.
                    </MudListItem>
                    <MudListItem>
                        <strong>Cramped-Synchronized:</strong> Rigid, simultaneous movements indicating high 
                        CP risk (specificity ~95%).
                    </MudListItem>
                </MudList>
            </MudItem>
            <MudItem xs="12" md="6">
                <MudList T="string" Dense="true">
                    <MudListItem>
                        <strong>Poor Repertoire:</strong> Monotonous, simple movements—moderate CP risk.
                    </MudListItem>
                    <MudListItem>
                        <strong>Normal Movements:</strong> Variable, complex, fluent movements indicating 
                        typical development.
                    </MudListItem>
                </MudList>
            </MudItem>
        </MudGrid>
    </MudPaper>

    <MudPaper Elevation="2" Class="pa-6 mb-6">
        <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" Class="mb-4">Technology Stack</MudText>
        <MudChipSet>
            <MudChip Color="Color.Primary" Size="Size.Small">.NET 9</MudChip>
            <MudChip Color="Color.Secondary" Size="Size.Small">ASP.NET Core</MudChip>
            <MudChip Color="Color.Tertiary" Size="Size.Small">Blazor</MudChip>
            <MudChip Color="Color.Info" Size="Size.Small">ML.NET</MudChip>
            <MudChip Color="Color.Warning" Size="Size.Small">ONNX Runtime</MudChip>
            <MudChip Color="Color.Success" Size="Size.Small">Cloudinary</MudChip>
        </MudChipSet>
    </MudPaper>

    <MudAlert Severity="Severity.Warning" Class="mb-6">
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
            <strong>Research & Screening Tool Only:</strong> CP-sight is designed to assist in screening and 
            should not replace professional medical diagnosis. All assessments should be validated by qualified 
            healthcare professionals trained in General Movements Assessment.
        </MudText>
    </MudAlert>

    <MudButton Variant="Variant.Filled" Color="Color.Primary" Href="/upload" StartIcon="@Icons.Material.Filled.Upload">
        Try CP-sight Now
    </MudButton>
</MudContainer>
